## What changed structurally
- The module is now split into 17 stages (was 9); every PR diff is 265-624
  lines. Ordering note: the feedback APIs intentionally come AFTER the
  calls dynamic-field stage so the ClickHouse value-semantics helpers
  (JSON_VALUE/casts/compare) land with the calls engine — the fixpoint
  assigns module helpers to their FIRST USE, so stage order controls
  which PR carries shared machinery.
- Test wiring (conftest --trace-server=fake, util predicates, skipif
  gates, AGENTS.md) now rides the FIRST branch; #7152 is closed and the
  andrew/fake-trace-server branch deleted. The fake is selectable from
  PR 1; the suite only fully passes with --fake at the top of the stack.
- skipif conversion: in-body gates became
  @pytest.mark.skipif(NOT_CLICKHOUSE_BACKEND, reason=...) decorators.
  NOT_CLICKHOUSE_BACKEND (tests/trace/util.py) is a pytest condition
  STRING evaluated at collection time with config in the namespace —
  fixture-based predicates can't run there. It mirrors
  get_trace_server_flag precedence (--clickhouse > --fake >
  --trace-server). Fixture-internal skips (ch_server,
  calls_complete/otel/ttl internal_server) stay as pytest.skip — pytest
  has no fixture-level skipif. client_is_clickhouse(client) remains for
  the two genuinely mid-test branches (dupe_select partial assertion,
  call_stats force_merge helper).
- test_large_keys_are_stripped_call previously early-RETURNED on the fake
  (counted as passed); it is now an honest skipif (passed->skipped, totals
  unchanged).

